Interface LoadablePage

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Page
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    LoginPage<T>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    MyAboutMePage

    public interface LoadablePage
extends Page
    A page that can be accessed directly, from a URL.

    Any implementor must implement (hide) getRelativeUrl().

    See Also:
    load(Class, WebDriver)

      • load

        static <T extends LoadablePage> T load(Class<T> loadablePageClass,
                                       org.openqa.selenium.WebDriver driver)
        Load the given LoadablePage. Browse to its URL, create its instance (which includes a wait until the page is loaded), and finally return it.
        Parameters:
        loadablePageClass - the class object for the requested page
        driver -
        Returns:
        the requested LoadablePage
        Throws:
        org.openqa.selenium.WebDriverException - if the page cannot be loaded
